On Tuesday, September 07, 2004, at 01:00AM, craig <vwbus(-at-)ckoon.org> wrote:

>while working on my rear hub today i ran across a snag (well, 
>several! but i digress...): the outer roller bearing on a 72 
>suspension - which is what is on the 70 - should be 211-501-283D. 

>my guess is perhaps the parts place messed up, 
>and they have 211-501-283 bearings in the box? these would be for a 
>68-70. if anyone has seen the two together, let me know if i am 
>correct :)

Measure them:

68-79 inner bearing (211 501 287, 6207-J or 207)
ID 35mm (1.3780) 
OD 72mm (2.8346) 
WIDTH 17mm (0.6693) 

71-79 outer bearing (211 501 283D, GRW111) 
ID 35mm (1.3780) 
OD 57mm (2.4409) 
WIDTH 19mm (0.7480) 

68-70 outer bearing (211 501 283, 1208S) 
ID 40mm (1.5748) 
OD 80mm (3.1496) 
WIDTH 18mm (0.7087)

